&lt;h2&gt;Clinical Rotational Pharmacist&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a forward thinking dynamic band 7 Clinical Pharmacist to join the extensive and varied rotation programme at Portsmouth Hospitals University Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The rotations include Surgery, Critical Care, Older People and Rehabilitation, Medical Admissions Unit, Renal, Oncology and Haematology, Medicine, Clinical trials, MSK and Women’s &amp; Children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During each rotation you will be supported in further developing your clinical knowledge and expertise under the direction of specialist pharmacists and an established team of medicines management technicians. You will also be able to develop your mentoring skills by supporting more junior members of the clinical team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post offers a wide range of development opportunities in a department that supports continuing professional development for all staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 13/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 27/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
